24/02/2011
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The newly appointed government is ready for talks with Serbia, Prime Minister Hashim Thaci said on Wednesday (February 23rd) during the cabinet's first meeting. 
"The dialogue, which will start in the near future, will be concluded with a better life for the citizens of Kosovo and the region, for a better European future, for a better future for our countries and peoples," Thaci said. 
The international community has been encouraging the start of Kosovo-Serbia talks since the autumn. 
(Klan Kosova, Kohavision, Arta TV, RTK - 23/02/11)
